\begin_layout Standard
Each transformation maps the whole square (the one with opposite corners
 
\begin_inset Formula $(0,0)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $(2,2)$
\end_inset

) to one of the parts of its dissection.
 You should recognize the 
\begin_inset Formula $2\times2$
\end_inset

 matrices as scaling by a factor of 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{1}{2}$
\end_inset

 in both horizontal and vertical directions.
 The addition of 
\begin_inset Formula $2\times1$
\end_inset

 vectors provide translations.
 In words, 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{4}$
\end_inset

 can be described as scaling by 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{1}{2}$
\end_inset

 horizontally and vertically followed by translation (shifting) 1 unit horizonta
lly.
 
